ell prey to a conflict between corporate rigidity and an unorganized, ill-informed, and over-enthusiastic civic administration and city council. Drawing on the private records of Rod Sykes, the CPR’s onsite negotiator and later Calgary’s mayor, Foran unravels the fascinating story of how politics ultimately undermined promise.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCanadian Pacific Railway Company-Planning-History-20th century. 0aEconomic development-Political aspects-Alberta-Calgary-History-20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh  abusiness history.  acity planning.  arailroad.  atransportation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013z978311127715840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781927356098423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781927356098/original  a978-3-11-127412-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-127715-8  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles